A RESOLUTION
1 Honoring the life and memory of Clarence "Ed" Barker; and for other purposes.
2 WHEREAS, Clarence "Ed" Barker was born in Augusta, Georgia, and raised in Warner
3 Robins, Georgia, where he demonstrated a strong work ethic from an early age, including
4 operating a gas station while in high school, setting a foundation for his lifelong dedication
5 to his community and family; and
6 WHEREAS, Ed dedicated nearly two decades of his life to public service, representing the
7 18th Senatorial District in middle Georgia for nine consecutive terms from 1973 to 1991,
8 during which he worked tirelessly to improve the lives of his constituents and strengthen the
9 State of Georgia; and
10 WHEREAS, Ed's leadership extended beyond politics as he served as president of the
11 Warner Robins Chamber of Commerce and the Air Force Association as well as continued
12 to contribute to the growth and prosperity of the community even after his political career;
13 and
